		&lt;p&gt;The two agents who shot Alex Pretti in the streets of Minneapolis have been identified: Jesus Ochoa and Raymundo Gutierrez.&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p&gt;Both were employed by Customs and Border Protection and assigned to Operation Metro Surge, the Trump regime&#39;s unprecedented deployment of armed and masked agents sent to sow terror into the hearts and minds of the American public. The move has led to massive protests in Minneapolis and around the country.&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p&gt;Department of Homeland Security Secretary Kristi Noem spread blatant lies about the execution of Pretti immediately after the incident, along with other representatives of the Trump regime. The government has tried to interfere with any investigation into the killing, despite the fact that videos of the event are readily available to the public that clearly expose the lies of the regime.&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p&gt;These are the exact same tactics the regime tried to unsuccessfully employ after Renee Good was killed by Jonathan Ross just a few weeks earlier. But every time their lies are exposed, their support base weakens, their power is threatened, and public outrage grows. It remains to be seen whether the public outcry will ultimately lead to the toppling of the regime, or if they will be able to escalate their terror tactics enough to suppress any effective opposition to the regime&#39;s power.&lt;/p&gt;
