    &lt;a href=&quot;/images/sx-RJndppy-800.webp&quot; class=&quot;lightbox-link&quot; aria-haspopup=&quot;dialog&quot; style=&quot;cursor:zoom-in&quot;&gt;
      &lt;img class=&quot;img-lightbox&quot; alt=&quot;Kennedy Center, 2010&quot; loading=&quot;lazy&quot; decoding=&quot;async&quot; style=&quot;--img-width:200&quot; src=&quot;/images/sx-RJndppy-200.webp&quot; width=&quot;800&quot; height=&quot;464&quot; srcset=&quot;/images/sx-RJndppy-200.webp 200w, /images/sx-RJndppy-800.webp 800w&quot; sizes=&quot;200px&quot;&gt;
    &lt;/a&gt;

            &lt;p class=&quot;caption&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;The John F. Kennedy Memorial Center for the Performing Arts.&lt;/b&gt; Image by &lt;a href=&quot;https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/User:Tom&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Tom&lt;/a&gt; from &lt;a href=&quot;https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Kennedy_Center_seen_from_the_Potomac_River,_June_2010.jpg&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Wikimedia Commons.&lt;/a&gt; Licensed under the &lt;a href=&quot;https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/3.0/deed.en&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Creative Commons Attribution 3.0 Unported license&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
		&lt;p&gt;Donny 2-Dolls thinks he&#39;s a brilliant businessman, but his lifelong habit of destroying the businesses he runs shows us otherwise. And his string of failed businesses continues even during his second term as president.&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p&gt;Last year, Trump took over control of the John F. Kennedy Center for the Performing Arts in Washington D.C. and renamed it to the &quot;The Donald Trump and the John F. Kennedy Memorial Center for the Performing Arts.&quot; The name itself is laughable due to the grammatical errors in the new name (It should read &quot;The Donald Trump and John F. Kennedy...&quot;) and the fact that the term &quot;memorial&quot; should only be used when the namesake is deceased.&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p&gt;What&#39;s even more laughable is the utter failure Donny 2-Dolls has made of the Center. Once a world-class venue for the performing arts, under Trump&#39;s leadership, the Kennedy Center has seen the lowest ticket sales in years, and a wave a cancellations of scheduled events. Under Trump&#39;s business leadership, the Kennedy Center can no longer remain in operation, and will close its doors for &quot;approximately&quot; two years.&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p&gt;Trump is claiming that the closure is to &quot;renovate&quot; the facility, but the timing is certainly questionable. Under this plan, the center will be closed until some time in 2028, and we can pretty well assume that it will remain closed until after the 2028 elections. Whether or not it reopens will no doubt depend on who wins that election.&lt;/p&gt;
