&lt;section class=&quot;block the-ugly&quot;&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;The ugly...&lt;/h4&gt;
	&lt;div class=&quot;blob&quot;&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;blob-title&quot;&gt;
        Trump announces plans for the federal government to take control of elections &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.ms.now/news/trump-suggests-federal-control-of-elections-in-some-areas&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;[Link&lt;span class=&quot;bi bi-link-45deg&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;]&lt;/a&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;blob-content&quot;&gt;
		&lt;p&gt;Donny 2-Dolls has been floating the idea of having Republicans &quot;take over&quot; election administration in &quot;some areas&quot; of the country.&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p&gt;The Constitution is very clear that elections are to be held by states without federal interference. Because of this, the president&#39;s announcements should raise alarm for anyone who believes in the rule of law and the validity of the Constitution of the Untied States of America.&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p&gt;Trump is claiming, without evidence (as always), that elections are &quot;unbelievably corrupt&quot; in &quot;some areas.&quot; There is no credible evidence of widespread fraud in this country&#39;s elections, and these claims are nothing more than blatant lies. FBI agents raided the Fulton County elections office in Georgia last week and took possession of official voter records from 2020, and will soon be making additional false claims that they have &quot;discovered&quot; fraud in these records, and will use this falsified evidence to claim that election fraud is a credible threat and that they have to nationalize the elections in order to ensure that their party &quot;wins&quot; the 2026 midterms.&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p&gt;One thing is absolutely clear: The threats to our elections are indications that the Trump regime knows that they will lose representatives in Congress in the 2026 mid-term elections, and they are going everything in their power to try to prevent a free and fair election this year. The video below is from the weekly &lt;i&gt;What&#39;s the Plan&lt;/i&gt; discussion hosted by &lt;i&gt;Indivisible&lt;/i&gt; co-executive directors Leah Greenberg and Ezra Levin. It&#39;s an hour-long video, but if you don&#39;t have time to watch the whole thing, watch the video from where it starts (5:03) until 8:53. Leah summarizes the regime&#39;s strategy and outlines how we can best fight against it.&lt;/p&gt;
