&lt;section class=&quot;block info&quot;&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;Keeping you informed...&lt;/h4&gt;
	&lt;div class=&quot;blob&quot;&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;blob-title&quot;&gt;
        The real story behind Trump&#39;s tariff war &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=RPzcGeiNYvk&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;[Link&lt;span class=&quot;bi bi-link-45deg&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;]&lt;/a&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;blob-content&quot;&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
		&lt;p&gt;For the past year, Trump has been using tariffs and the threats of tariffs to manipulate the economy of the United States. One day, he&#39;s threatening massive tariffs, and the next day he&#39;s delaying or dropping those tariffs.&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;While we all know that Donny 2-Dolls is a fool, these actions are not just the result of his incompetence, but they are part of a larger strategy from his handlers to control the United States economy to benefit the current regime and its sycophants.&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;Trump uses the threats of tariffs to turn his power into personal profits. He threatens to impose tariffs on foreign goods, which threatens the profits of foreign companies. They respond by making large contributions to Trump&#39;s campaign or investing in his various grifts. If their bribe is considered acceptable, Trump will make an exception to the tariffs for those companies. Trump ends up making more money, the companies that bribe him have a competitive advantage over their rivals, and the American people are left to pay the price.&lt;/p&gt;
