&lt;section class=&quot;block the-good&quot;&gt;
	&lt;h4&gt;The good...&lt;/h4&gt;
	&lt;div class=&quot;blob&quot;&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;blob-title&quot;&gt;
        Protests expand, closing schools and businesses to oppose Trump regime &lt;a href=&quot;https://apnews.com/article/immigration-protests-64fd52ba5283e8f56c57dddb1c3a3852&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;[Link&lt;span class=&quot;bi bi-link-45deg&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;]&lt;/a&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;blob-content&quot;&gt;
        &lt;div class=&quot;image-right&quot; style=&quot;width:225px&quot;&gt;

    &lt;a href=&quot;/images/ugs6XUMOS5-800.webp&quot; class=&quot;lightbox-link&quot; aria-haspopup=&quot;dialog&quot; style=&quot;cursor:zoom-in&quot;&gt;
      &lt;img class=&quot;img-lightbox&quot; alt=&quot;protestors holding sign reading &#39;Minnesota shut it down! The people have the power to stop ICE terror!&#39;&quot; loading=&quot;lazy&quot; decoding=&quot;async&quot; style=&quot;--img-width:200&quot; src=&quot;/images/ugs6XUMOS5-200.webp&quot; width=&quot;800&quot; height=&quot;533&quot; srcset=&quot;/images/ugs6XUMOS5-200.webp 200w, /images/ugs6XUMOS5-800.webp 800w&quot; sizes=&quot;200px&quot;&gt;
    &lt;/a&gt;

            &lt;p class=&quot;caption&quot;&gt;Image by &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.flickr.com/photos/44550450@N04/55069629476/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Fibonacci Blue&lt;/a&gt; from &lt;a href=&quot;https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Protest_against_ICE_in_downtown_Minneapolis_-_The_People_Have_the_Power_to_Stop_ICE_Terror.jpg&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Wikimedia Commons.&lt;/a&gt; Licensed under the &lt;a href=&quot;https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/4.0/deed.en&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Creative Commons Attribution-Share Alike 4.0 International license&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;Nationwide protests erupt over the brutal slayings of Alex Pretti and Renee Good by ICE agents in Minneapolis as violence against civilians continues to escalate. On Friday, Americans around the country took to the streets again to protest the Trump regime&#39;s fascist takeover of this country. Schools and businesses in several states have closed in a grass-roots general strike intended to shut down the economy.&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;These protests have been organized primarily in response to ICE violence in Minnesota, but across the country, dissatisfaction with the Trump regime&#39;s policies continues to grow. Another &quot;No Kings&quot; protest is planned for Saturday, March 28. The last &quot;No Kings&quot; protest was the largest single day of protest in the history of the United States, and it is expected that the protest on March 28 will be even larger.&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;For many people, these protests feel like they are not working as the Trump regime continues to abuse its power and further demolish our democratic institutions and deny us our constitutional rights. But it&#39;s vitally important that we keep up the momentum and continue to organize and let the world know that we do not accept the current state of affairs. This is not the United States of America that any of us want to live in. So we must stay the course. Stay angry, stay loud, and make your voice heard at every opportunity. We&#39;re all afraid, we&#39;re all tired, and we&#39;re all feeling a bit hopeless. And that&#39;s exactly what the regime wants. They want to wear us down, to make us feel like nothing will ever change. They want us to accept what they are doing as the new normal. No matter what happens, we can never allow our opposition to be silenced. Find a protest, find a group, take a stand, and let the world know that you stand for liberty and justice for all.&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;div&gt;
