&lt;section class=&quot;block the-bad&quot;&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;The bad...&lt;/h4&gt;
	&lt;div class=&quot;blob&quot;&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;blob-title&quot;&gt;
        Trump regime arrests journalists to intimidate the free press &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/law/2026/jan/30/press-freedom-journalist-arrests-ice-don-lemon&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;[Link&lt;span class=&quot;bi bi-link-45deg&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;]&lt;/a&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;blob-content&quot;&gt;
        &lt;div class=&quot;image-right&quot; style=&quot;width:225px&quot;&gt;

    &lt;a href=&quot;/images/GtRK1V9I41-200.webp&quot; class=&quot;lightbox-link&quot; aria-haspopup=&quot;dialog&quot; style=&quot;cursor:zoom-in&quot;&gt;
      &lt;img class=&quot;img-lightbox&quot; alt=&quot;1958 US postage stamp: Freedom of the Press&quot; loading=&quot;lazy&quot; decoding=&quot;async&quot; style=&quot;--img-width:200&quot; src=&quot;/images/GtRK1V9I41-200.webp&quot; width=&quot;200&quot; height=&quot;307&quot;&gt;
    &lt;/a&gt;

        &lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;The Trump regime has arrested four independent journalists after they covered an anti-ICE protest in Minnesota: Don Lemon, Trahern Jeen Crews, Georgia Fort, and Jamael Lydell Lundy. These arrests were made despite the fact that multiple judges refused to approve the baseless arrest warrants. These reporters were exercising their right to report on matters of public interest, which is a fundamental pillar of a free press. The arrests are a clear indication that the Trump regime is attempting to intimidate and silence journalists who are doing their jobs.&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;Civil rights activists are outraged by this blatant attempt to silence the press. Reverend Al Sharpton accused the Trump regime of taking a &quot;sledge hammer [to] the knees of the First Amendment.&quot; Lemon and Fort are both independent journalists, Crews is the co-founder of Black Lives Matter Minnesota and former candidate for mayor and state representative, and Lundy is a candidate for Minnesota Senate District 65.&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;The journalists were covering a peaceful protest at Cities Church in Minneapolis, Minnesota. Demonstrators disrupted a church service earlier this month because one of the staff members is a field office director for ICE. Protesters were there to point out the hypocrisy of a church that claims to follow the teachings of Jesus, the Prince of Peace, while openly supporting the ever-increasing violence of ICE in particular and the Trump regime in general.&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;blockquote&gt;
            &lt;p&gt;As journalists, our first obligation is to bear witness and to inform. When those obligations are met with detention or prosecution instead of protection, we must ask: &#39;What message are we sending about who gets to report and who gets silenced?&#39;&lt;/p&gt;
            &lt;figcaption class=&quot;blockquote-footer&quot;&gt;Errin Haines, &lt;i&gt;President of National Association of Black Journalists&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/figcaption&gt;
        &lt;/blockquote&gt;
        &lt;div&gt;
            &lt;div class=&quot;related-links&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;Related Links:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
            &lt;ul class=&quot;related-links&quot;&gt;
                &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/law/2026/jan/30/press-freedom-journalist-arrests-ice-don-lemon&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;(The Guardian) press freedom groups denounce arrests of two journalists including Don Lemon after Minnesota anti-ICE protest&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
                &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.pbs.org/newshour/politics/trump-administration-charges-don-lemon-with-federal-civil-rights-crimes-related-to-anti-ice-church-protest&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;(PBS) Trump administration charges Don Lemon with federal civil rights crimes related to anti-ICE church protest&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
            &lt;/ul&gt;
