&lt;section class=&quot;block the-bad&quot;&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;The bad...&lt;/h4&gt;
	&lt;div class=&quot;blob&quot;&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;blob-title&quot;&gt;
        More than a month after the deadline to release the Epstein Files has passed and less than 1% have been released &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2026/jan/24/legal-experts-epstein-files-release-congress&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;[Link&lt;span class=&quot;bi bi-link-45deg&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;]&lt;/a&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;blob-content&quot;&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
		&lt;p&gt;On November 19,  Congress passed a law called the &quot;Epstein Files Transparency Act&quot; that ordered the Attorney General to &quot;make publicly available in a searchable and downloadable format all unclassified records, documents, communications, and investigative materials in the possession of the Department of Justice&quot; that relate to Jeffrey Epstein within 30 days. That deadline came and went on December 19th. This week marked the passage of a full month since that deadline.&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p&gt;So, has the Trump regime obeyed the law passed by Congress and signed by Donny 2-Dolls?&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p&gt;No. Less than 1% of the files have been released to date, and the few files that were released since the passage of the law are mostly documents that have already been released to the public previously. Despite going to war with Venezuela, threatening to take Greenland by force from our own NATO ally, and sending thousands of armed thugs into Democratic cities to terrorize and murder United States citizens right here at home, the Trump regime just can&#39;t seem to make people forget about the Epstein Files.&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p&gt;This is a major issue for the Trump regime because Donny 2-Dolls ran on campaign promises to release the Epstein Files, and some of his sycophants have become slightly less ardent in their support of the Trump regime as he&#39;s continually refused to keep that promise.&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p&gt;What can be done to force the Trump regime to obey the laws it has passed? There&#39;s not much that can make an immediate difference, but steady and ongoing legal pressure to force the regime to provide legal justification for its refusal to comply with the law and ongoing public pressure can eventually force the regime&#39;s hand. But it won&#39;t happen any time soon, and it won&#39;t be easy.&lt;/p&gt;
