    &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;blob-content&quot;&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;Florida Governor Ron DeSantis&#39; administration spent over $35 million in taxpayer funds that were allocated for child welfare and medical services for political consulting and advertising campaigns to oppose ballot initiatives he opposed.&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;While the governor is entitled to his own political opinions, the use of public funds previously allocated to other purposes is a misuse of taxpayer funds and violates the principle of accountability in government. &lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;Professor emeritus Kenneth Goodman, former director of medical ethics at the University of Miami declared the spending of child welfare funds on &quot;undermining the will of the voters&quot; amounts to &quot;corruption at the expense of children.&quot;&lt;/p&gt;
