&lt;p&gt;Recap of this week in the revolution: Kilmar Abrego Garcia free again. Trump regime&amp;#39;s exposes its own hypocrisy. U.S. citizenship on sale now and U.S. military seizes Venezuelan oil tanker. Beware of surveillance pricing when shopping online.&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;section class=&quot;block the-good&quot;&gt;
	&lt;h4&gt;The good...&lt;/h4&gt;
	&lt;div class=&quot;blob&quot;&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;blob-title&quot;&gt;
        Kilmar Abrego Garcia freed from immigration detention &lt;a href=&quot;https://apnews.com/article/abrego-garcia-el-salvador-deportation-31160936c51932f74b717eb1143edd55&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;[Link&lt;span class=&quot;bi bi-link-45deg&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;]&lt;/a&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;blob-content&quot;&gt;
        &lt;div class=&quot;image-right&quot; style=&quot;width:225px&quot;&gt;
            &lt;img class=&quot;img-link&quot; alt=&quot;Kilmar Abrego Garcia, 2025&quot; loading=&quot;lazy&quot; decoding=&quot;async&quot; style=&quot;--img-width:200&quot; src=&quot;/images/uwXNjfjBMC-200.webp&quot; width=&quot;200&quot; height=&quot;247&quot;&gt;
            &lt;p class=&quot;caption&quot;&gt;Kilmar Abrego Garcia, from his meeting with Senator Chris Van Hollen on April 17, 2025, in El Salvador.&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
		&lt;p&gt;On March 12, Kilmar Abrego Garcia was arrested by a DHS agent. Three days later, he was sent to a torture prison in El Salvador despite a court order specifically prohibiting his deportation to El Salvador. Despite the fact that he was &quot;accidentally&quot; deported, the Trump regime refused to bring him back to his home in the United States and falsely claimed that he was a member of a terrorist organization. The Supreme Court ordered the regime to effectuate Abrego Garcia&#39;s return. The Trump regime still refused to take action to bring Abrego Garcia home. They fought against the ruling, but after months of failed arguments and unaccepted excuses, they did arrange to bring Abrego Garcia back to the United States.&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p&gt;But the persecution didn&#39;t stop there. The Trump regime doubled-down on their false allegations that Abrego Garcia was a member of a terrorist organization and when he was returned to the United States, it was to face criminal charges. He remained in prison for several months before being returned to his home state of Maryland. Three days later, he was detained again at a routine check-in, and has been imprisoned since then while the Trump regime has repeatedly threatened to deport him to any country other than El Salvador.&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p&gt;This week, Abrego Garcia&#39;s habeas petition was granted and a federal judge ordered his release from custody. But Kilmar Abrego Garcia is one of the most blatant examples of the Trump regime&#39;s incompetence and cruelty, so there is no doubt that they will try again to find some excuse to continue his persecution.&lt;/p&gt;
