&lt;section class=&quot;block info&quot;&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;Keeping you informed...&lt;/h4&gt;
	&lt;div class=&quot;blob&quot;&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;blob-title&quot;&gt;
        Retailers exploit your personal data to overcharge you using surveillance pricing &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=-cbtUYshYM8&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;[Link&lt;span class=&quot;bi bi-link-45deg&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;]&lt;/a&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;blob-content&quot;&gt;
		&lt;p&gt;From airlines to groceries to rideshares to televisions, online shoppers are being exploited by surveillance pricing. Retailers use your private data, collecting all of your personal data together from all of your browser and mobile data points, to calculate the highest price you are willing to pay for a product or service, and then they charge that price. Meanwhile, the next person may be paying significantly less for the exact same product or service.&lt;/p&gt;
