		&lt;p&gt;Back in September, Donny 2-Dolls ordered US attorney Erik Siebert to bring criminal charges against former FBI Director James Comey for lying to Congress. But Siebert found insufficient evidence to file charges against Comey and eventually resigned before he could be fired. Trump then replaced him with a completely unqualified insurance lawyer named Lindsey Halligan, who has no experience prosecuting criminal cases and apparently not enough integrity to turn down the appointment she is woefully unqualified for.&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p&gt;While seeking a grand jury indictment of Comey, Halligan showed &quot;a disturbing pattern of profound investigative missteps,&quot; according to Judge William E. Fitzpatrick. As a result of Halligan&#39;s bungling, Fitzpatrick has had to go to extraordinary lengths to provide Comey&#39;s defense team with all grand jury materials pertaining to the case. This information is typically sealed until the trial commences, but Halligan&#39;s mistakes jeopardized the integrity of the proceedings and could potentially be viewed as misconduct, which may lead to the entire case being thrown out without a trial.&lt;/p&gt;
