        &lt;p&gt;Of the 600 individuals still being detained after months of brutal raids across Chicago over the past few months, only 16 (2.6%) had any criminal history at all, and none of those criminal charges included offenses that the Trump regime has previously described as the &quot;worst of the worst&quot; (such as rape and murder).&lt;/p&gt;
