&lt;section class=&quot;block the-ugly&quot;&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;The ugly...&lt;/h4&gt;
	&lt;div class=&quot;blob&quot;&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;blob-title&quot;&gt;
        Trump regime&#39;s blatant abuse of power &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.propublica.org/article/trump-pardons-clemency-george-santos-ed-martin&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;[Link&lt;span class=&quot;bi bi-link-45deg&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;]&lt;/a&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;blob-content&quot;&gt;
        &lt;div class=&quot;image-right&quot; style=&quot;width:225px&quot;&gt;
            &lt;img class=&quot;img-link&quot; alt=&quot;Abuse of power&quot; loading=&quot;lazy&quot; decoding=&quot;async&quot; style=&quot;--img-width:200&quot; src=&quot;/images/lgFvXdea7o-200.webp&quot; width=&quot;200&quot; height=&quot;160&quot;&gt;
            &lt;p class=&quot;caption&quot;&gt;Image by &lt;a href=&quot;https://pixabay.com/users/mohamed_hassan-5229782/?utm_source=link-attribution&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_campaign=image&amp;utm_content=6570152&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Mohamed Hassan&lt;/a&gt; from &lt;a href=&quot;https://pixabay.com//?utm_source=link-attribution&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_campaign=image&amp;utm_content=6570152&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Pixabay&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;Donny 2-Dolls has been using his powers to grant clemency to benefit his own supporters, donors, and fellow felons. From insurrectionists to fraudsters to money launderers, the only requirement for a Trump pardon appears to be offering him loyalty or financial gain.&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;Meanwhile, the established procedure for requesting a presidential pardon has been mostly ignored. Those who are following established Justice Department rules in their requests for pardons are ignored, while those who end up with a pardon usually never even went through the established process. After pardoning Binance founder Changpeng Zhao, Trump admitted that he didn&#39;t even know him, and only pardoned him because &quot;a lot of people asked me to.&quot;&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;The pardons not only erase the criminal record of the recipients. They also erase any judgments of restitution. Estimates are that the pardons issued over the past 10 months have erased more than $1.3 billion in restitution owed to victims of the crimes being pardoned.&lt;/p&gt;
